Ansuria Moodley, a South African in the city of Dnipro in Ukraine spoke with eNCA's Dan Moyane about the situation on the ground. Courtesy of #DStv403  KIEV - South Africans stuck in Ukraine are experiencing the devastating effects of the Russia-Ukraine conflict. Food and water are running out. READ: South Africans in Ukraine desperate to come home Many are not able to leave following the invasion by Russian soldiers. Meanwhile, President Cyril Ramaphosa called for mediation between Russia and Ukraine to end the military action. Ramaphosa says it's time for the UN Security Council to step up.